To enable the Commissioner to determine compliance with this subtitle, a licensee shall make and preserve the following books, accounts, and records for a period of at least 7 years:
A general ledger containing all assets, liability, capital, income, and expense accounts;
Each debt management services agreement between the licensee and a consumer;
Books and records for each consumer with whom the licensee has a debt management services agreement;
Bank statements and bank reconciliation records;
A copy of each written summary required under § 12-916(a)(1)(i)2 of this subtitle; and
A copy of each signed acknowledgment required under § 12-916(a)(1)(i)3 of this subtitle.
